      <h1 class='title'>Great Chagos Bank: Environmental Protection</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 31 March 2004 vol 659 c62WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_62ws' title='Col. 62WS &mdash; HL Deb 31 March 2004 vol 659 c62WS' name='column_62ws' href='#column_62ws' rel='bookmark'>62WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0659P0-09659'>
        <a name='S5LV0659P0_20040331_LWS_4'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-elizabeth-symons' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040331_LWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Ms Elizabeth Symons' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-elizabeth-symons" title="Ms Elizabeth Symons">Baroness Symons of Vernham Dean</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0659P0-09659">The Great Chagos Bank, which lies within the waters adjacent to the outer islands of the British Indian Ocean Territory (BIOT), is an exceptional example of a submerged coral atoll, providing a valuable contribution to the marine ecology of the Indian Ocean. On 17 September 2003, in order to help to conserve the natural resources of the bank, the Commissioner for BIOT proclaimed an area including the Great Chagos Bank to be an environmental (preservation and protection) zone. A copy of the proclamation, together with the relevant chart and co-ordinates, has been deposited with the UN under Article 75 of UNCLOS, and wilt be published in the Law of the Sea Bulletin No. 54.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
